<ns3232:section xmlns:ns3232="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.introduction.j2eeApis.jca">

  <ns3233:title xmlns:ns3233="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The Java 2 Connector Architecture (JCA)</ns3233:title>
  <ns3234:para xmlns:ns3234="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The Java Connector Architecture specifies a standard API for obtaining connections to
    connection-oriented resources like databases and messaging services.
  </ns3234:para>
  <ns3235:para xmlns:ns3235="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    This is also typically used to integrate with legacy systems (such as mainframes,
    ERP, etc) by building managed, object-oriented adaptors to those systems.
  </ns3235:para>
</ns3232:section>